EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL PROCEDURE -- IDENTIFICATION AND APPREHENSION OF
CRIMINALS
***
1 This act would require the superior court clerk to automatically seal cases or individual
2 counts of a criminal complaint or indictment that were dismissed, upon request of the defendant
3 and would require the clerks in the district and superior courts to serve the orders upon the bureau
4 of criminal identification, the arresting law enforcement agency and provide two (2) certified copies
5 to counsel of record.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
